My Post-Chemical Peel Skincare Routine

Starting with the basics I use the Rice Water Face Wash. It’s super gentle and works great for oily skin.

Next up is the Snail Mucin Serum. After a chemical peel, the skin tends to get really dry and patchy, and this has honestly helped keep my skin hydrated and calm.

Then comes sunscreen I’ve been using the Clayco Sunglaze Sunscreen. It’s lightweight, non-sticky, and perfect for oily skin. The best part? It doubles as both a moisturizer and sunscreen.

Lastly, I use the Clinique Even Better Eye Cream. It didn’t feel super effective in the beginning, but with consistent use, I’ve started noticing visible results.

That’s all for now

All the outfits is from Myntra under rs 2000/-

XS Blue sleeveless : Fit’s on point, lil transy but super summer friendly. Comfy cotton, neutral vibes—9/10, loved it!

M Orange: Colour may vary, heavy cotton, comfy but def not lightweight—hella oversized.

M light Blue Stripes: Evergreen piece, never flops. Breezy fit, soft cotton blend—fitted, forever vibe.

S Light Green: Fully transy—layer it up. Fab shiny fabric, office to party ready, just a lil pricey.

L Pink: Chill wear goals. Oversized, cute AF color, all day err day fit.

M Yellow: Fabric? Chef’s kiss. Breathable, subtle yellow—summer happy vibe, oversized.

S Beige Satin Shirt: My ultimate fav, classy chic, office to after hours, fitted and fire.

XL navy Blue: Hardcore corporate girlie energy—too formal for me but cute. Oversized.

XXL Green: Loose, comfy, plus-size baddie approved. Love the chill vibe.
